Russia Equity Movers: Gazprom, Lukoil, Rosneft Shares Are Active

-- B y   J a c k   J o r d a n
-- 
2011-07-19T15:15:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-19/russia-equity-movers-gazprom-lukoil-rosneft-shares-are-active.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  climbed 0.7
percent to 1,700.13 at the 6:45 p.m. close in Moscow, the
biggest jump since July 7. The dollar-denominated RTS Index
gained 1.2 percent to 1,926.23.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Gazprom (GAZP RX),  Russia ’s gas export monopoly, gained
1 percent to 199.87 rubles, paring its biggest drop in three
weeks yesterday. Russia will consider opportunities for
increasing direct gas supplies to  Europe  as  Germany  and other
countries shift away from nuclear power, Energy Minister Sergei
Shmatko said in Hannover late yesterday.  OAO Lukoil (LKOH RX), Russia’s second-biggest oil producer,
gained 0.9 percent to 1,826.40 rubles. OAO Rosneft (ROSN RX),
the country’s largest crude producer, advanced 1.3 percent to
232.06 rubles. OAO Surgutneftegas (SNGSP RX) preferred shares
jumped 1.6 percent to 14.055 rubles. China said its apparent
fuel consumption rose 7.2 percent in the first half, driving a
2.3 percent rally in  oil prices  to $98.11 a barrel.  -- Editors: Alex Nicholson, Linda Shen  To contact the reporter on this story:
